snippet.textDisplay:
I am tired.

I am tired of life.
I am tired of having to live up to what people think of me.
I am tired of feeling like a bother to anyone.
I am tired of feeling worthless.
I am tired I am not good at anything.
I am tired of switching from one passion to another just to be disappointed from failures.
I am tired of people critising me.
I am tired of other people's judgement.
I am tired of hurting myself.
I am tired to always work when I feel I will just fall from exhaustion.
I am tired I mentally cannot show my true colors.
I am tired of feeling scared that people will judge me.
I am tired of feeling ugly, having an ugly face or body.
I am tired I don't have any dreams to chase.
I am tired I don't have a goal.
I am tired I don't have a purpose.
I am tired I am lost.
I am tired of being so negative.
I am tired I am not positive enough.
I am tired that I can't be more funny to entertain others.
I am tired of being around people who are better than me because it makes me think thats who I could've been.
I am tired of disappointing.
I am tired of the same life over and over again.
I am tired of working hard towards something only to get a failing grade.
I am tired of having to wear a mask to cover me.
I am tired that I don't have any true friends.
I am tired of crying in secret.
I am tired that I put in effort to care for others, but I don't get the same treatment.
I am tired of being alone.
I am tired of always being broken.
I am tired of my parents not supporting me.
I am tired of asking questions like
Why am I here right now?
Why am I doing this?
Why did I use to have ambitions but I suddenly lost love in everything?
Why did I use to love but not it was a past childhood memory?
How did I go from innocent and pure to anxiety and depression?
I feel tired that I can't accomplish anything that holds meaning to me.
I feel useless.
I feel like a burden to everyone around.
I feel people's disappointment and disgust when they look at me.
I want people to think of me like a good person.
I want to feel life again. I watch multiple discipline videos, and life changing things, and I get motivated for a couple weeks. I have a reason to keep again, but I lose sight.
I want to stop thinking of ways I can die right now pain free.
I have fallen so hard to the grind that I am commenting to the Internet.
It felt nice expressing my true feelings to someone. Something I haven't done in years beside maybe writing it down.
I hate being tired.
I wish something in this one life would give me energy.
But I don't know what it is.
I guess I will stay lost.

But I am just so tired.
